article.headline: Mississippi Valley St. 64, Grambling St. 55
article.story: ITTA BENA, Miss. (AP) -- Richard Cannon scored 15 points and Mississippi Valley State strengthened its grip on first place in the Southwestern Athletic Conference with a 64-55 win over Grambling State on Monday night. Kadrian Bryant scored 14 and Jefferey Price and Stanford Speech each added 11 for the Delta Devils (15-14, 12-5) in the victory over the Tigers (10-13, 8-8). Mississippi Valley State led 37-25 at halftime on its way to opening a two-game lead over its nearest conference opponent with less a week to go in the regular season. Andre Ratliff led the Tigers with 16 points and Anthony Williams scored 12. No other member of the team had more than seven points.
